article.headline: S. Dakota St. 86, CS Bakersfield 65
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. -- Anthony Cordova was one of five South Dakota State players in double figures Tuesday as the Jackrabbits rolled to an 86-65 men's basketball win over Cal State-Bakersfield. Cordova was 7-for-11 from the field on his way to 16 points for SDSU (5-7). Kai Williams added 14 points and nine rebounds, Clint Sargent 12 points, Garrett Callahan 11 and Dale Moss 10. SDSU shot 55 percent from the field and made five of its eight 3-pointers in the first half to take a 49-24 halftime lead. The Roadrunners (3-8), who have lost six straight games, countered with a 33-percent effort in the first half. They made just three of 12 3-pointers in the game. Santwon Latunde was the only Bakersfield player in double figures with 16 points and nine rebounds. The Roadrunners' leading scorer, Trent Blakely was held to two points, 12 points below his average.
